# Component patterns

Composition patterns that recur across the product. Not primitives — these are higher-level structures.

## Pattern — Action bar

**Shape:** `<Card>` + `<h2>` + right-aligned `<Button>` row
**When:** settings section, list header
**Example:** {{path_to_canonical_example_in_repo}}

## Pattern — Form row

**Shape:** `<FormField>` (label + input + helper + error) stacked
**When:** any form field
**Example:** {{...}}

## Pattern — Inline action confirmation

**Shape:** button → confirm state (button changes to `<>Cancel> <>Confirm>`) → success toast
**When:** destructive actions that don't warrant a modal

## Anti-patterns to avoid

- Deeply nested cards-in-cards (visual noise + unclear hierarchy)
- Modals inside modals
- Mixed loading states on the same page (some skeletons, some spinners)
- Inline error messages that disappear on focus (user loses context)

